To find the $x$-intercept we set $y=0$ and solve for $x$. This gives us $3(0) - 4x = 12$, and so $x = -3$. The $x$-intercept is the point $\boxed{(-3, 0)}.$ [asy]
import graph;
defaultpen(linewidth(0.6)+fontsize(10));
real x = -4;
pair P = (-3, 0);
xaxis(0, 2.5, Ticks(" ", 1.0));
yaxis(-1, 0.5, Ticks(" ", 0.5));
pair A = x*dir(180), B = x*dir(0);
draw(A--B);
dot(P);
label("(0,0)", P, NE);
[/asy]
